{
  "texts": [
    "It is mainly used for time series modeling of sign language and has achieved good results.",
    "During this period, research on sign language recognition mainly focused on recognizing fingerspelling sign language and isolated static sign language (gesture).",
    "The datasets were obtained from data gloves.",
    "In the second stage (approximately from 2012 to the present), CNN, 3D-CNN, YOLO, and various deep neural networks (such as ResNet, VGG-Nets, Faster R-CNN, CapsNet, etc.) have sprung up.",
    "At this stage, research on sign language recognition mainly focuses on large-scale sign language and real-time, continuous sign language recognition."
  ]
}